    <h2 id=3D"section-1" class=3D"section-header">1. Executive Summary</h2>
    <p>
      The F&amp;B Financial Performance Projection Engine (FPE) is a specia=
lized SaaS platform designed to model, forecast,
      and optimize the financial performance of dark kitchen networks. Unli=
ke generic FP&amp;A tools, FPE captures the
      specific unit economics of food delivery platforms (aggregators), kit=
chen capacity constraints, hyper-local demand
      curves, and multi-market expansion dynamics.
    </p>

    <h3>Primary Users</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Founder/CEO:</strong> Strategic direction, fundraising, e=
xpansion decisions.</li>
      <li><strong>CFO:</strong> Financial planning, cash management, capita=
l allocation, board reporting.</li>
      <li><strong>COO:</strong> Operational capacity planning, unit economi=
cs optimization.</li>
      <li><strong>Commercial Lead:</strong> Pricing strategy, marketing spe=
nd allocation, demand forecasting.</li>
      <li><strong>Analyst:</strong> Scenario modeling, data maintenance, va=
riance analysis.</li>
      <li><strong>Board/Investor:</strong> Oversight, performance monitorin=
g (read-only).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Evolution from v1 to v3</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Feature/Aspect</th>
          <th>v1 (Original Concept)</th>
          <th>v2 (Refined Scope)</th>
          <th>v3 (Unified Master)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Core Philosophy</strong></td>
          <td>Operational/Transaction-heavy</td>
          <td>Finance-First Planning</td>
          <td>Unified Finance-First + Strategic Intelligence</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Architecture</strong></td>
          <td>Flat module structure</td>
          <td>6-Layer Hierarchy</td>
          <td>10-Layer Comprehensive Stack</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Data Model</strong></td>
          <td>~40 tables</td>
